The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
Archives
 Corporate Briefs
																								 Theatre chain PVR Ltd has acquired a 30 per cent stake in a joint venture with Amit Burman to set up food courts in the country and participate in the food retailing business. Burman, one of the promoters of the Dabur group, is creating a food retailing company, with its own brands. It also plans to secure franchisees of international food brands.																								 Financial Technologies (India) Limited has reported a 1024 per cent rise in total income at Rs 461 crore for the quarter ended September 30, 2007, compared with Rs 41 crore for the quarter ended September 30, 2006. The EBITDA margin rose 96 per cent and profit after tax increased 1189 per cent to Rs 338.5 crore from Rs 26.25 crore during the same period.																								 Siemens has bagged a Rs 87-crore order from McNally Bharat for Rashtriya Ispat Nigam Ltds (RINL) steel plant in Vizag. Siemens will supply electricals for RINLs sinter plant, that is scheduled to be commissioned by August 2009. 																								 Firstsource Solutions Limited has launched foreign currency convertible bonds worth $275 million. The fund will be used to repay the $275-million debt for its recent acquisition of MedAssist Holdings Inc. The FCCBs are expected to be listed on the Singapore Exchange Securities Trading Ltd. JP Morgan and ICICI Bank acted as the joint book-runners.																								 Husco International has opened an R amp;D and manufacturing centre at Talegaon industrial park near Pune. The company makes hydraulic amp; electro hydraulic controls for construction, industrial, automotive and farm equipment.																								 Sunil Hi-Tech Engineers Ltd has registered a net profit of Rs 5.24 crore in the second quarter against Rs 1.30 crore a year ago. Operating profit was Rs 11.59 crore compared with Rs 3.75 crore in the year-ago period. Net sales rose to Rs 69.79 crore from Rs 33.32 crore.																								 Flamingo Pharmaceuticals has launched a range of formulations including anti-infectives, gastroenterologicals and orthocare in Calcutta and other cities of the state. Flamingo is targeting a 1 per cent market share in eastern India on an annual basis.																								 Core Projects and Technologies Ltd has posted a profit after tax of Rs 22.39 crore for the quarter ended September 30 against Rs 5.87 crore a year ago. Total sales have increased to Rs 114.63 crore from Rs 30.28 crore in the year-ago period.																								 AOL has launched Truveo, a video search engine. It has also introduced AOL Hindi and Tamil portals on http://www.aol.in. ADVERTISEMENT
